10.1. Domain Exclusivity Provision

   a. While the original project is actively maintained and accessible at any of its official domains, no public instances of this software may be hosted on any other domain or subdomain.

   b. The official domains for this project are:
      - [DOMAIN 1]
      - [DOMAIN 2]
      - [ADDITIONAL DOMAINS AS NEEDED]

   c. Temporary maintenance periods or technical outages of the official domains do not constitute abandonment of the exclusivity provision.

   d. The exclusivity provision terminates only if:
      - The original project is officially announced as retired or abandoned by the copyright holder, OR
      - All official domains have been inaccessible for a continuous period of 180 days without any announcement of temporary maintenance.

   e. Private instances for personal use that are not accessible to the public internet are permitted at any time.

   f. Upon termination of the exclusivity provision, other instances may be hosted on public domains, provided they comply with all other terms of this license.

10.2. Open Source Requirement

   a. The project must remain open source under this license or a compatible open source license.

   b. All source code, assets, and documentation must be made publicly available in a source code repository.

10.3. Funding Restrictions

   a. If the project is officially retired or abandoned, no funding may be solicited or accepted for instances of this software without explicit written permission from the original project owner(s).

   b. "Funding" includes but is not limited to donations, crowdfunding, investments, sponsorships, or any form of monetary compensation specifically for operating instances of this software.

10.4. Contributor Rights and Credit

   a. By submitting code, assets, or other contributions to this project, contributors transfer all rights to their contribution to the project owner(s).

   b. Contributors retain the right to be credited for their contributions in the project's documentation, attribution notices, or other appropriate locations.

   c. The project owner(s) may use, modify, distribute, or otherwise exploit contributions without further permission or compensation to contributors.

10.5. License Modification Authority

   a. The project owner(s) reserve the right to modify these additional terms or the license as a whole at any time.

   b. License modifications will apply to all future contributions and uses of the software.

   c. Existing distributions of the software under previous license terms remain compliant with those terms.

